title: For Sale:  Colt Officers Model Special -.38 special
postcontent:
The Officer's Model Special was the fouth issue of the Officer's Model, and was Colt's first upgrade post-war.  Post-war Colt began assigning letter codes to frame sizes.  The Officer's Model Special was made only from 1949 to 1952.  It had an extra heavy, untapered "Bull" barrel and the Coltmaster fully adjustable rear sight that was offered only on this revolver.  A new style hammer was introduced, and the post-war type cylinder retention system was used.  Checkering of the hammer, trigger, and cylinder latch was discontinued. 
This one's serial number gives it an 1950 date of manufacture.  It is in really good shape.  This gun has been used for what it was designed, giving it a slight bluing wear at the end of the barrel, other than that the bluing is in great shape.  It has Pachmayr grips that are in good shape.  Feel free to email me with any questions and I'll get back to you as quickly as I can.  Asking $650 OBRO. Willing to ship, but buyer pays shipping costs.

title: For Sale:  Parallax Tactical PXTreme Gen4 M-16 TiN Titanium Nitrite Complete BCG
postcontent: This is a bolt carrier with a TiN shaft and a Nickel Boron coated bolt.  Please note that the depicted bolt carrier group features a TiN bolt, while the bolt of the current generation is Nickel Boron coated.  The advantage of a Nickel Boron bolt is that it's softer than the Titanium Nitride bolt, thus reducing wear on your barrel extension (where the bolt lugs lock into the barrel) and improving the overall life of your weapon.  Visually, the NiB bolt appears silver instead of gold. The bolt carrier itself is plated with Titanium Nitride, which is the yellow-gold color you see in the pictures below. TiN is an extremely hard ceramic material, often used as a coating on titanium alloys, tool steel, stainless steel, carbon steel and other metallic components to improve the substrate's surface properties.  Common applications include aerospace parts, military components, medical implants, cutting tools, industrial parts, manufacturing dies / molds and dental and orthodontic appliances.  TiN is a beautiful gold color and is often used as a wear resistant alternative to elemental gold plating.  Applied as a thin coating, TiN is used to provide a hard surface to protect cutting and sliding surfaces and for decorative purposes (due to its gold appearance).  It is also used as a non-toxic barrier on the exterior of medical implants and jewelry.  TiN has a low coefficient of friction and an operating temperature of more than 1,000 degrees Fahrenheit.  In most applications a coating of less than 5 micrometers (0.00020 in) is applied.   We apply TiN using a technique called cathodic arc PVD, or physical vapor deposition.  This method is environmentally friendly and produces a functional coating unlike some other methods which are strictly decorative in nature.  Our coatings comply with aerospace specification AMS 2444A. Benefits of TiN coating:   Hard, scratch and wear resistant Lubricious, corrosion and chemical resistant Beautiful gold color No appreciable build-up to interfere with firearm operation Cost effective alternative to Gold plating
